<h1>Latest news 2021-09-05</h1>

 <h2>NuTyX 21.09.0 available with cards 2.4.136</h2>
  <p>
   The NuTyX team is happy to announce the new version of NuTyX 21.09.0 and cards 2.4.136.
  <p>
   The xorg-server graphics server version 1.20.13,
   the Mesa 3D library in 21.2.1, gtk3 3.24.30
   and qt 5.15.2.
  <p>
   The python interpreters are en 3.9.6 et 2.7.18.
  <p>
   The XFCE desktop environment is updated to version 4.16.
  <p>
   The MATE desktop environment is a 1.26 version .
  <p>
   The GNOME desktop environment is also updated to version 40.4.
  <p>
   The KDE desktop environment is available in Plasma 5.22.5, Framework 5.85.0 and applications in 21.08.1.
  <p>
   Available browsers are: firefox 91.0.2, chromium 92.0.4515.159, epiphany 40.3, etc
  <p>
   Many desktop applications have been updated as well like thunderbird 78.13.0, Scribus 1.5.7, libreoffice 7.1.5.2, gimp 2.10.24, etc. 
  <p>
   Core NuTyX ships with Long Term Support (LTS) kernels:
   4.9.282, 4.14.246, 4.19.206, 5.4.144 and 5.10.62
   and the latest stable version 5.14.1 .
  <p>
   The kernel change logs are available here:
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v4.x/ChangeLog-4.9.282">kernel 4.9.282 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v4.x/ChangeLog-4.14.246">kernel 4.14.246 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v4.x/ChangeLog-4.19.206">kernel 4.19.206 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v5.x/ChangeLog-5.4.144">kernel 5.4.144 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v5.x/ChangeLog-5.10.62">kernel 5.10.62 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v5.x/ChangeLog-5.14.1">kernel 5.14.1 changelog</a>
  <p>
   ISOs are available in LXDE, XFCE4, GNOME, MATE, KDE5, BASE and MINI (those last two propose command line interface only without graphical interface).
  <p>
   They are available on the <a href="downloads">download page.</a>

 <h2>What's up ?</h2>

  <h3>The upgrade-nutyx command</h3>
   <p>
    The upgrade-nutyx command offer the possibility to upgrade automatically your NuTyX.
    A scheduled task planned every 30 minutes as default check for any updates.
    Availables packages for update are installed at next shutdown of the PC.
    To install upgrade-nutyx package, a;
    </p><pre class="command_user"><kbd>sudo cards install upgrade-nutyx</kbd></pre>
    will do it.
    Just run it ones with your own account.
    Explainations will be found in the post-install of the package.
    
  <h3>The package manager cards</h3>
   <p>
    The cards search command shows now all the sub-packages as well if success packages found.
    
  <h3>The collections</h3>
   <p>
    In order to simplify the configuration of NuTyX, the <i>desktops</i> collection is now integrated into the <i>gui-extra</i> collection.
   <p>
    Means NuTyX does use 5 official collections now.
  <h3>Others</h3>
   <p>
   A discussion forum is back in service in a more NuTyX theme like.
    
 <h2>Upgrade process</h2>
  <p>
   Even if NuTyX 21.09.0 is a minor release.
 </p><pre class="command_user"><kbd>sudo cards upgrade</kbd></pre>
  <p>
   Once the upgrade process done,
   the "desktops" collection in the <i>/etc/cards.conf</i> file will be deleted automatically
  <p>
   Many NuTyX wallpapers are now included by default.

 <h2>Thanks</h2>
  <p>
   Thanks to Spiky for his patience and his generosity in upgrading all thoses many packages.

